[[Image:Strode spartacus.JPG|thumb|right|300px|Woody Strode in ''Spartacus'' (1960)]]
 
As an actor, the 6' 4" (1.93 m) Strode was noted for film roles that contrasted with the stereotypes of the time. He is probably best remembered for his brief Golden Globe-nominated role in ''[[Spartacus (1960 film)|Spartacus]]'' (1960) as the Ethiopian [[gladiator]] Draba, in which he fights [[Kirk Douglas]] to the death.
